^BGray Elven or Niramaa^b
This language is directly descended from TrueSpeech and is a
quiet,tonal language. It is spoken in the areas around
Allece,Canias,Felice,Culmaiea,& Leeward. 

^BCaliphate^b
A quick semispoken language with many clicking consonants. Spoken in
the areas around the kaylin Mts.,The Leeward Cape, The Eastern of
Culmaiea,and down along the coast south of Culmaiea. 

^BMantic^b
Also known as old Karmadic. A low toned, solidlanguage with little
poetry involved in it. It is spoken by the humans of Isig, Oen and
some parts of Ymris. Most of the Northernmost lands use it except for
Meremont. Also used by the humans of the northern of dwarvish
kingdoms.

^BSans ^b
A seagoers language. Used by the Kol, some of the western islands and
many of the southernmost tradertowns. 

^BOsterole^b
A most poetic language Spoken in Roke and most of the eastern islands.

^BKargan^b
A singular language with few uses. Very gutteral in nature. Spoken in
the plains below the Val-Tier Mts and in San-Sir. 

^BBasque^b
The language of the Val-Tier. 

^BHardic^b
The language of the Mimbrate pennisula and surrounding environs.
Definitely a polite and courteous language. 

^BAroyan^b
The flowing part halfling speech of the overlook mountains. 

^BSarin^b
The language of Osterland and Temeroth.            

 
